<img width="412" height="250" class="wp-image-319251" style="width: 600px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Maku2.jpg" alt="" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Maku2.jpg?width=412&amp;auto_optimize=medium 412w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Maku2-300x182.jpg?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Maku2-197x120.jpg?width=197&amp;auto_optimize=medium 197w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Maku2-200x121.jpg?width=200&amp;auto_optimize=medium 200w" sizes="(max-width: 412px) 100vw, 412px" /> By David Odama The former minister of Information, Labaran Maku has announced his withdrawal from the Governorship race after voting has commenced in Nasarawa Local government of Nasarawa state. Maku said after wider consultations with friends and associates, he has decided to withdraw from the contest. On whether there are other reasons for his withdrawal, the former minister said  his withdrawal is best known to him adding that reasons behind his withdrawal would be made available soon.  “I decided to withdraw from the contest after due consultations with my family, political associates and other stakeholders. “My opinion, the process of the primary election  is ongoing” the former minister said